ADDITIONAL DISCLAIMER FOR ENCRYPTION/CLOUD BACKUP SOFTWARE 
================================================================================ 
IMPORTANT: Please read this entire section before using this software. 
1. ENCRYPTION KEY MANAGEMENT - CRITICAL - If you forget your encryption key, YOUR DATA IS UNRECOVERABLE - We cannot recover, reset, or bypass lost encryption keys - No backup of encryption keys is maintained - You are fully responsible for key management - Lost keys = permanent data loss - Use a password manager to store your key 
2. NO DATA LOSS LIABILITY In no event shall the developer be liable for: - Any data loss of any kind - Inability to restore encrypted data - Loss of encryption keys - Incomplete backups or sync failures - Any damages arising from use of this software 
3. DRIME CLOUD SERVICE DEPENDENCY - This software depends on Drime's API and services - Drime may change their API without notice - Drime may discontinue service - We have no control over Drime's services - We are not responsible for Drime's actions - Drime's privacy policy and terms apply to your data 
4. NO WARRANTY FOR DATA SECURITY - No guarantee of encryption strength - No guarantee of protection against all attacks - Browser-based encryption has limitations - No professional security audit has been performed - Use at your own risk 
5. NOT SUITABLE FOR - Medical records (HIPAA compliance) - Financial data (PCI-DSS compliance) - Legal documents with privilege - Highly classified information - Any situation where data loss is unacceptable 
6. TESTING REQUIRED - Test all backup and restore procedures thoroughly - Test with non-critical data first - Verify data integrity after restore - Do not rely on untested backups 
7. USER RESPONSIBILITY By using this software, you acknowledge: - You use it entirely at your own risk - You understand the security limitations - You have tested backup/restore before relying on it - You are responsible for your encryption key - You will not rely solely on this software for critical backups
